HEADWORD: Foregut
<hw>Fore"gut`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>The anterior part of the alimentary canal, from the mouth to the
intestine, or to the entrance of the bile duct.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

